HEADWORD: Immission
<hw>Im*mis"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>immissio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>immission</ets>. See
<er>Immit</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of immitting, or of sending or
thrusting in; injection; -- the correlative of
<inv>emission</inv>.</def>⟦br⟧
